OL,3,C'Wake-up call': World climate body
OL,4,Cconfirms 2024 was hottest year ever
OL,6,F"While a single year above 1.5 C of
OL,7,Fwarming does not indicate that the
OL,8,Flong-term temperature goals of the
OL,9,FParis Agreement are out of reach, it
OL,10,Fis a wake-up call that we are
OL,11,Fincreasing the risks to our lives,
OL,12,Feconomies and to the planet," said WMO
OL,13,FSecretary-General Celeste Saulo.
OL,15,FHer words were echoed by United
OL,16,FNations Secretary-General Antonio
OL,17,FGuterres who said: "Our planet is
OL,18,Fissuing more distress signals -- but
OL,19,Fthis report shows that limiting long-
OL,20,Fterm global temperature rise to 1.5
OL,21,Fdegrees Celsius is still possible.
