OL,6,FAround 90% of the heat trapped by
OL,7,Fgreenhouse gasses is stored in the
OL,8,Fsea, pushing its temperature to record
OL,9,Flevels and causing the largest loss of
OL,10,Fglacier ice recorded over a three-year
OL,11,Fperiod.
OL,13,FThe melting ice has contributed to the
OL,14,Frate of sea level rise that's doubled
OL,15,Fsince satellite measurements began.
OL,17,FThe environmental impacts of global
OL,18,Fwarming directly effect large amounts
OL,19,Fof people as places become
OL,20,Finhospitable, arid or destroyed by
OL,21,Fclimate induced extreme weather events.
