OL,6,FSimilarly, in the US, Hurricanes
OL,7,FHelene and Milton caused economic
OL,8,Flosses of tens of billions of dollars.
OL,9,FOver 200 deaths were associated with
OL,10,Fthe exceptional rainfall and flooding
OL,11,Ffrom Helene, the most since Hurricane
OL,12,FKatrina in 2005.
OL,14,FIn Mozambique, 100,000 people were
OL,15,Fdisplaced by Tropical Cyclone Chido.
OL,17,FWildfires and food insecurity,
OL,18,Fexacerbated by a hotter planet, have
OL,19,Falso contributed to global disruption.
